1
00:00:05,741 --> 00:00:07,341
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,341 --> 00:00:09,041
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:10,271 --> 00:00:11,411
Oh no.

4
00:00:13,581 --> 00:00:16,711
- Emergency board meeting.
- All of a sudden?

5
00:00:17,081 --> 00:00:19,381
Don't tell me
they're selling off FG.

6
00:00:19,681 --> 00:00:23,091
Come on, Mr. Hwangbo
is in our Fashion Division.

7
00:00:23,351 --> 00:00:24,791
There's no way they'd touch it.

8
00:00:26,761 --> 00:00:30,231
By the way, is Ms. Kim not in yet?

9
00:00:30,831 --> 00:00:31,861
What?

10
00:00:34,701 --> 00:00:35,701
What's this?

11
00:00:36,301 --> 00:00:38,271
It says Ms. Kim resigned.

12
00:00:38,741 --> 00:00:39,841
You've got to be kidding.

13
00:00:40,071 --> 00:00:43,311
She says she's sorry
for leaving without saying goodbye.

14
00:00:44,211 --> 00:00:46,141
A message just popped
up in the group chat.

15
00:00:48,111 --> 00:00:49,111
Gosh.

16
00:00:49,911 --> 00:00:50,951
Kim So Hye.

17
00:00:55,281 --> 00:00:58,221
- Ms. Gong.
- So Hye, what are you doing here?

18
00:00:58,621 --> 00:01:00,661
I heard you were launching
your own brand, Ms. Gong...

19
00:01:00,921 --> 00:01:02,361
so I came to work with you.

20
00:01:02,831 --> 00:01:04,431
You're saying you resigned?

21
00:01:04,961 --> 00:01:05,961
Yes.

22
00:01:06,831 --> 00:01:10,471
So Hye, are you crazy?
You quit a perfectly good company?

23
00:01:10,531 --> 00:01:14,001
Your brand is going to take
the fashion world by storm...

24
00:01:14,071 --> 00:01:16,171
and I want to be a founding member.

25
00:01:16,941 --> 00:01:19,541
What are you talking about?
Go back to the office. Now.

26
00:01:20,311 --> 00:01:21,341
Unbelievable.

27
00:01:22,411 --> 00:01:24,251
Ms. Gong, wait up.

28
00:01:34,521 --> 00:01:36,161
Warehouse vibes.

29
00:01:36,861 --> 00:01:37,931
So Hye.

30
00:01:38,191 --> 00:01:42,271
- I have nothing prepared yet.
- So we should do it together.

31
00:01:43,931 --> 00:01:46,501
Should I go buy cleaning supplies
right away?

32
00:01:46,871 --> 00:01:49,411
Go to work. Stop being so reckless.

33
00:01:51,941 --> 00:01:54,241
You need someone with practical
experience right away.

34
00:01:54,681 --> 00:01:57,911
I really want to repay you
for everything. Please?

35
00:01:57,981 --> 00:02:00,081
Gosh.

36
00:02:01,151 --> 00:02:03,491
I don't even know
how much I can pay you.

37
00:02:03,791 --> 00:02:06,221
The salary isn't for me to decide.

38
00:02:06,921 --> 00:02:10,131
Then is there someone
else funding this?

39
00:02:10,431 --> 00:02:11,591
Yes.

40
00:02:12,931 --> 00:02:14,161
Hold on.

41
00:02:14,831 --> 00:02:19,001
I found a studio. The address
is Onjeong-gu, Onjeong...

42
00:02:19,001 --> 00:02:20,071
What? Seriously?

43
00:02:20,071 --> 00:02:23,141
- Director Yang is your investor?
- Yes.

44
00:02:23,471 --> 00:02:27,711
What is this sudden romantic twist?

45
00:02:27,941 --> 00:02:31,811
- No romance. Strictly business.
- Right.

46
00:02:32,051 --> 00:02:33,821
I don't really get it either,

47
00:02:33,881 --> 00:02:35,751
but he said it was a decision
for the Fashion Division.

48
00:02:41,821 --> 00:02:43,631
They're shutting down
the Fashion Division?

49
00:02:44,291 --> 00:02:46,101
And selling off FG?

50
00:02:47,301 --> 00:02:49,271
What shocks me more is that...

51
00:02:49,331 --> 00:02:51,771
Mr. Hwangbo sided with
Director Baek.

52
00:02:51,871 --> 00:02:56,071
How could he say
the Fashion Division is useless?

53
00:02:56,311 --> 00:02:58,011
I heard Mr. Hwangbo
was transferred...

54
00:02:58,071 --> 00:02:59,581
to the Strategic Planning Division.

55
00:02:59,781 --> 00:03:02,041
He's Executive Director Hwangbo now.

56
00:03:02,451 --> 00:03:04,881
The Vice President
must've been furious.

57
00:03:05,751 --> 00:03:07,451
I heard she was beyond livid.

58
00:03:15,761 --> 00:03:16,991
Hey.

59
00:03:17,131 --> 00:03:19,661
(Taehan Group.)

60
00:03:20,201 --> 00:03:23,531
- You bastard.
- Let go. Let's talk, ma'am.

61
00:03:23,601 --> 00:03:28,171
Ma'am? Hey, how could you do this?

62
00:03:28,701 --> 00:03:29,711
Don't you know what...

63
00:03:29,711 --> 00:03:31,241
the Fashion Division meant
to our father?

64
00:03:31,571 --> 00:03:32,981
How could you,
right after he passed away,

65
00:03:33,041 --> 00:03:36,081
betray us? You, of all people?

66
00:03:36,511 --> 00:03:39,981
Betrayal? It was a decision
for the Group's survival.

67
00:03:40,051 --> 00:03:41,051
What?

68
00:03:41,121 --> 00:03:42,991
The Fashion Division has already
lost its competitive edge.

69
00:03:43,051 --> 00:03:46,561
There's no point in keeping people
on a sinking ship, is there?

70
00:03:46,621 --> 00:03:48,891
Were you just pretending
to be on our side...

71
00:03:48,961 --> 00:03:50,931
to get your hands on
my father's inheritance?

72
00:03:52,661 --> 00:03:53,761
Let's go. Come on.

73
00:03:53,831 --> 00:03:57,431
You better stay out
of my sight from now on.

74
00:03:57,601 --> 00:04:00,201
If I see you again,
I swear I'll kill you.

75
00:04:00,571 --> 00:04:02,041
Gosh, seriously.

76
00:04:13,081 --> 00:04:16,251
Thanks to you, we got rid
of the founding business.

77
00:04:16,691 --> 00:04:17,691
If it hadn't been for you...

78
00:04:17,751 --> 00:04:19,991
the board members were about
to side with Director Yang.

79
00:04:20,561 --> 00:04:24,061
Thank you for making the right
decision for Taehan.

80
00:04:25,291 --> 00:04:28,131
The Vice President won't
back down that easily.

81
00:04:28,561 --> 00:04:30,031
Then we'll have to take care of her.

82
00:04:30,301 --> 00:04:33,071
Starting with Director Yang,
the thorn in your side?

83
00:04:38,371 --> 00:04:39,711
I like you more and more.

84
00:04:41,111 --> 00:04:42,311
Leave it to me.

85
00:04:45,551 --> 00:04:47,521
Pacu Nacho, you really didn't know?

86
00:04:47,821 --> 00:04:49,821
When did that jerk
get in bed with Director Baek?

87
00:04:49,891 --> 00:04:53,521
How should I know?
I feel backstabbed too.

88
00:04:55,061 --> 00:04:56,891
This is what happens
when you put stupid ideas...

89
00:04:56,961 --> 00:04:58,391
in his head about being undercover.

90
00:04:58,531 --> 00:05:01,501
Are you saying Jun Hyeok
betrayed us because of me?

91
00:05:01,561 --> 00:05:06,101
No, no. What are we going to do now?

92
00:05:06,341 --> 00:05:08,201
It was a decision made
at the Group level...

93
00:05:08,271 --> 00:05:10,341
so we have no choice
but to accept it for now.

94
00:05:10,541 --> 00:05:12,411
Are you really going
to be so irresponsible?

95
00:05:12,941 --> 00:05:15,911
Gosh, my poor father must be
so appalled right now...

96
00:05:15,981 --> 00:05:20,251
he can't even rest in peace.
And what about the design team?

97
00:05:20,321 --> 00:05:22,621
They're about to be kicked
out onto the street.

98
00:05:23,521 --> 00:05:24,521
What do we do?

99
00:05:25,451 --> 00:05:26,691
- Goodness.
- Goodness.

100
00:05:27,861 --> 00:05:30,461
What's going to happen to us?

101
00:05:30,831 --> 00:05:32,731
Are we all getting fired?

102
00:05:34,061 --> 00:05:35,061
Yes.

103
00:05:35,431 --> 00:05:38,871
The sale terms don't include
employee transfers.

104
00:05:39,201 --> 00:05:42,341
The termination process
will begin sequentially.

105
00:05:43,711 --> 00:05:45,211
As for a special
compensation package.

106
00:05:45,271 --> 00:05:48,511
I'll negotiate a special payout
on top of your severance.

107
00:05:48,781 --> 00:05:50,811
It was all for nothing.

108
00:05:50,911 --> 00:05:52,621
If it was all going
to end like this...

109
00:05:52,681 --> 00:05:55,181
why did we work ourselves
to death trying to hang on?

110
00:05:56,351 --> 00:05:58,091
But what about Kim So Hye?

111
00:05:58,321 --> 00:06:00,291
Do you think she resigned
because she knew something?

112
00:06:05,761 --> 00:06:08,401
Is that for real?

113
00:06:10,701 --> 00:06:14,501
FG sold, Fashion Division shut down.

114
00:06:16,111 --> 00:06:17,571
Because a Gong Ju Ah brand...

115
00:06:17,571 --> 00:06:20,011
will be the spark that revives
the Fashion Division.

116
00:06:20,081 --> 00:06:21,311
You asked me to protect...

117
00:06:21,311 --> 00:06:23,881
the Taehan Fashion Division,
didn't you?

118
00:06:24,081 --> 00:06:26,981
That's what I'm doing right now,
protecting the Fashion Division.

119
00:06:30,951 --> 00:06:32,621
He knew all along.

120
00:06:33,361 --> 00:06:35,761
That's why he rushed
the brand launch.

121
00:06:41,931 --> 00:06:44,171
- This is insane.
- What?

122
00:06:44,231 --> 00:06:46,471
They say Mr. Hwangbo
sank our division.

123
00:06:46,841 --> 00:06:47,971
Mr. Hwangbo...

124
00:06:48,441 --> 00:06:52,841
- Park Jun Hyeok?
- They say he betrayed them.

125
00:06:53,011 --> 00:06:56,411
Gosh, that's absurd.
I can't believe he...

126
00:06:59,451 --> 00:07:00,581
Woo Jae? What is it?

127
00:07:00,721 --> 00:07:03,521
Where are you right now?
Can you come home?

128
00:07:03,751 --> 00:07:05,321
I'm busy right now. Why?

129
00:07:05,421 --> 00:07:06,591
The substation called
and asked us...

130
00:07:06,661 --> 00:07:07,661
to come identify Grandfather.

131
00:07:07,961 --> 00:07:11,361
What? So they found Grandfather?

132
00:07:16,601 --> 00:07:18,601
(Respect for Human Rights,
Fairness, and Kindness)

133
00:07:22,511 --> 00:07:24,411
Father.

134
00:07:28,581 --> 00:07:30,011
Father.

135
00:07:32,081 --> 00:07:34,681
(Warm and Reliable Police)

136
00:07:34,751 --> 00:07:38,251
Am I your father?

137
00:07:46,261 --> 00:07:51,071
Father, it's me.
I'm your eldest son.

138
00:07:51,501 --> 00:07:54,371
It's Jeong Han.
You don't remember me?

139
00:07:58,041 --> 00:08:02,241
Father, it's me,
your second son, Dae Han.

140
00:08:02,311 --> 00:08:03,711
Father, do you remember me?

141
00:08:06,881 --> 00:08:08,151
I don't know you.

142
00:08:09,391 --> 00:08:10,821
I don't remember.

143
00:08:12,861 --> 00:08:15,831
It seems he jumped out of
Jo Mi Hyang's car...

144
00:08:15,891 --> 00:08:17,761
when it stopped at a light.

145
00:08:17,991 --> 00:08:20,161
Then he hailed a taxi
and told the driver...

146
00:08:20,231 --> 00:08:21,601
to take him to your hospital.

147
00:08:21,731 --> 00:08:25,231
How on earth did you end up here?

148
00:08:25,331 --> 00:08:27,401
Apparently, all he had on him
was this piggy bank.

149
00:08:27,471 --> 00:08:28,471
So the taxi driver...

150
00:08:28,541 --> 00:08:30,111
brought him here
to the Police Substation.

151
00:08:32,611 --> 00:08:36,551
Let's take him home.
Mom must be waiting. Hurry.

152
00:08:40,721 --> 00:08:42,891
I killed someone.

153
00:08:45,491 --> 00:08:47,961
My name is Jo Mun Sik.
I killed someone...

154
00:08:47,991 --> 00:08:49,891
so I've been living in hiding.

155
00:08:52,131 --> 00:08:54,231
He's said that over and over...

156
00:08:54,301 --> 00:08:56,771
but he doesn't actually
remember anything.

157
00:08:57,701 --> 00:09:00,241
My sister said so.
She said I killed someone.

158
00:09:00,501 --> 00:09:02,671
Father.

159
00:09:02,741 --> 00:09:06,541
It seems Jo Mi Hyang fed him
lies to keep him isolated.

160
00:09:06,611 --> 00:09:09,211
So even though he doesn't
remember doing it...

161
00:09:09,511 --> 00:09:12,111
he thinks he's a murderer?

162
00:09:12,481 --> 00:09:16,191
To know for sure, we'll have to
hear it directly from Jo Mi Hyang.

163
00:09:16,521 --> 00:09:19,891
His identity has been confirmed,
so you can take him with you.

164
00:09:19,991 --> 00:09:21,891
We'll contact you
for the witness interview.

165
00:09:22,631 --> 00:09:23,991
Father.

166
00:09:24,891 --> 00:09:25,901
Why...

167
00:09:26,531 --> 00:09:28,161
- Father.
- Father.

168
00:09:30,431 --> 00:09:33,901
(Onjeong Market)

169
00:09:33,971 --> 00:09:36,941
Father. This is Onjeong Market.

170
00:09:44,611 --> 00:09:46,121
Oh my goodness.

171
00:09:46,321 --> 00:09:50,191
My goodness, you're
Dr. Gong Gi Cheol, right?

172
00:09:50,391 --> 00:09:54,391
Oh my, it is him. It's Dr. Gong.

173
00:09:54,461 --> 00:09:58,361
Yes, that's right. He's our father.
We finally found him.

174
00:09:59,261 --> 00:10:01,231
Do you remember me, Dr. Gong?

175
00:10:01,501 --> 00:10:03,731
You always told me not to
eat late-night snacks...

176
00:10:03,801 --> 00:10:07,241
and scolded me for
eating salty food.

177
00:10:07,501 --> 00:10:09,271
What about me, Dr. Gong?

178
00:10:09,571 --> 00:10:12,611
When I used to work
at the fish market...

179
00:10:12,741 --> 00:10:15,141
you used to come by all the time.

180
00:10:15,951 --> 00:10:17,881
Excuse me.

181
00:10:18,051 --> 00:10:21,421
He can't remember things
from the past right now.

182
00:10:21,481 --> 00:10:23,421
- Oh, really?
- Yes.

183
00:10:23,491 --> 00:10:25,521
Was he in an accident?

184
00:10:25,961 --> 00:10:29,091
Wait, don't tell me he doesn't
even remember his family?

185
00:10:29,461 --> 00:10:32,431
- No.
- Oh no, that's terrible.

186
00:10:32,491 --> 00:10:34,261
Oh, so that's what happened.

187
00:10:34,701 --> 00:10:37,931
That must be why he couldn't
come home for 30 years.

188
00:10:38,331 --> 00:10:42,071
- Oh dear.
- Let's say hello next time.

189
00:10:42,401 --> 00:10:43,711
Right.

190
00:10:43,771 --> 00:10:47,241
I'm sorry. Yes, we'll see you soon.

191
00:10:47,541 --> 00:10:48,541
Let's go.

192
00:10:50,181 --> 00:10:53,721
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

193
00:10:56,091 --> 00:11:00,421
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

194
00:11:00,491 --> 00:11:02,591
Mom. Honey.

195
00:11:21,511 --> 00:11:22,681
Gi Cheol.

196
00:11:24,181 --> 00:11:26,321
It's me. Seon Hae.

197
00:11:28,321 --> 00:11:29,851
Mom.

198
00:11:30,351 --> 00:11:31,521
Don't you...

199
00:11:32,721 --> 00:11:34,321
remember me?

200
00:11:36,431 --> 00:11:37,431
No.

201
00:11:39,161 --> 00:11:40,501
You don't?

202
00:11:53,381 --> 00:11:54,981
Where have you been?

203
00:11:56,511 --> 00:11:58,781
How could you come back like this?

204
00:11:59,721 --> 00:12:01,781
- Mom.
- Mother.

205
00:12:02,751 --> 00:12:03,921
I'm sorry.

206
00:12:16,331 --> 00:12:17,531
(Missing Person)

207
00:12:17,531 --> 00:12:20,441
(We are looking for
Dr. Gong Gi Cheol.)

208
00:12:20,601 --> 00:12:22,001
Oh, this?

209
00:12:22,711 --> 00:12:24,771
We put that up to find you, Father.

210
00:12:26,941 --> 00:12:28,241
I guess we can take this down now.

211
00:12:28,511 --> 00:12:29,711
Yes. Right.

212
00:12:42,191 --> 00:12:43,491
Father.

213
00:12:45,161 --> 00:12:46,831
Father. They found Dr. Gong.

214
00:12:47,531 --> 00:12:49,431
They found Jeong Han's father.

215
00:12:49,831 --> 00:12:54,671
- What? They found Gi Cheol?
- Yes. He just got back.

216
00:12:58,571 --> 00:13:00,541
Are you in pain...

217
00:13:00,611 --> 00:13:02,581
or uncomfortable anywhere?

218
00:13:02,851 --> 00:13:05,411
I'm not in pain. I'm fine.

219
00:13:06,381 --> 00:13:10,321
Father. If you're in pain,
you have to tell us.

220
00:13:10,691 --> 00:13:13,491
That's how we can treat you
and prescribe medicine.

221
00:13:13,991 --> 00:13:17,531
I don't like medicine.
It makes my head fuzzy.

222
00:13:18,531 --> 00:13:20,001
Gosh.

223
00:13:22,871 --> 00:13:26,101
Oh, yes. Honey.

224
00:13:28,201 --> 00:13:30,111
Is this all the
medicine Father was taking?

225
00:13:30,711 --> 00:13:32,941
Not all of it. I pulled up
the prescriptions...

226
00:13:33,011 --> 00:13:34,841
Jo Mi Hyang filled
in the last few years.

227
00:13:37,611 --> 00:13:40,381
There are a lot of
over-the-counter painkillers.

228
00:13:40,381 --> 00:13:41,651
In case of an overdose...

229
00:13:41,721 --> 00:13:43,691
How could she give him
only these meds?

230
00:13:44,391 --> 00:13:47,121
I wonder if she even
followed the proper dosage.

231
00:13:47,391 --> 00:13:49,261
He must have been in pain,
unable to go to a hospital...

232
00:13:49,321 --> 00:13:50,431
just enduring it with medication.

233
00:13:50,761 --> 00:13:52,491
First, let's schedule
a health checkup.

234
00:13:53,161 --> 00:13:55,731
We need a brain MRI
and a CT scan too.

235
00:13:56,971 --> 00:13:58,731
Gi Cheol. Gong Gi Cheol!

236
00:13:59,301 --> 00:14:00,941
- You're here.
- You're here?

237
00:14:02,941 --> 00:14:04,711
My goodness.

238
00:14:13,051 --> 00:14:14,151
You've gotten old.

239
00:14:16,351 --> 00:14:17,621
Just as old as me.

240
00:14:20,961 --> 00:14:23,091
Live long enough,
and we do meet again.

241
00:14:24,361 --> 00:14:27,231
Father,
I can recognize him right away.

242
00:14:27,301 --> 00:14:30,631
- He still has the same face.
- I'm so glad you're here.

243
00:14:34,441 --> 00:14:36,171
You all worked so hard to find him.

244
00:14:37,371 --> 00:14:38,371
- Right.
- Right.

245
00:14:39,041 --> 00:14:41,841
Gi Cheol will get better soon.

246
00:14:42,741 --> 00:14:44,181
Yes, he has to.

247
00:14:46,221 --> 00:14:47,381
Hey, Gong Gi Cheol.

248
00:14:47,781 --> 00:14:51,521
I promise I'll get your memory back.

249
00:14:52,051 --> 00:14:53,121
Got it?

250
00:14:53,691 --> 00:14:54,691
Yes.

251
00:14:55,491 --> 00:14:56,491
You rascal.

252
00:14:57,291 --> 00:14:58,931
Even though I'm a year older...

253
00:14:59,501 --> 00:15:01,761
you called me your friend
and dropped formalities.

254
00:15:01,831 --> 00:15:02,971
Now that you've lost your memory,

255
00:15:03,031 --> 00:15:04,071
you're using formalities with me?

256
00:15:15,441 --> 00:15:18,781
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

257
00:15:18,981 --> 00:15:22,851
Let's get Father new glasses
before we go home.

258
00:15:22,921 --> 00:15:24,051
Good idea.

259
00:15:24,451 --> 00:15:26,121
They must be uncomfortable,
right, Father?

260
00:15:26,421 --> 00:15:27,621
I'm fine.

261
00:15:27,921 --> 00:15:30,131
Let's just get him
new lenses for now.

262
00:15:30,261 --> 00:15:32,861
Okay. Let's do that,
Father. All right?

263
00:15:33,501 --> 00:15:34,561
Thank you.

264
00:15:49,981 --> 00:15:51,181
Father.

265
00:15:52,281 --> 00:15:55,281
Do you know where we are?

266
00:15:59,191 --> 00:16:01,921
- This is our home, Father.
- Yes.

267
00:16:11,131 --> 00:16:15,041
- Hello, Grandfather.
- I'm your grandson, Woo Jae.

268
00:16:15,401 --> 00:16:18,111
Grandfather, I'm Ju Ah.

269
00:16:18,411 --> 00:16:20,611
The Ju Ah you used to adore.

270
00:16:22,111 --> 00:16:24,051
I don't know anything.

271
00:16:24,911 --> 00:16:26,981
I can't remember anything.

272
00:16:31,451 --> 00:16:33,561
- Father...
- Father, what's wrong?

273
00:16:33,721 --> 00:16:35,121
Father, what's wrong?

274
00:16:36,291 --> 00:16:40,431
He's overwhelmed by too much
information at once.

275
00:16:42,261 --> 00:16:45,331
Take your time, Father.
There's no rush.

276
00:16:45,831 --> 00:16:49,911
- That's right.
- I'm sorry I can't remember.

277
00:16:50,271 --> 00:16:51,411
I'm so sorry.

278
00:16:52,041 --> 00:16:55,481
No, Father, it's okay.
Just take it slow, okay?

279
00:16:58,081 --> 00:16:59,111
Let's get you inside.

280
00:17:02,451 --> 00:17:03,651
You should go in too, Mother.

281
00:17:07,321 --> 00:17:09,061
I'll brew some Memory Tonic
right away.

282
00:17:09,831 --> 00:17:13,601
It'll restore his strength
and clear his mind.

283
00:17:14,431 --> 00:17:15,461
Are you happy?

284
00:17:16,131 --> 00:17:17,771
Of course I am...

285
00:17:18,331 --> 00:17:20,541
My friend is back after 30 years.

286
00:17:20,941 --> 00:17:23,341
But I'm worried
he's lost his memory.

287
00:17:23,471 --> 00:17:28,041
At our age, anything can happen.
What's a little memory loss?

288
00:17:35,581 --> 00:17:37,951
What's your take on his condition?

289
00:17:39,121 --> 00:17:40,521
On top of the amnesia...

290
00:17:40,921 --> 00:17:43,591
the long-term isolation
and continuous mental control...

291
00:17:43,591 --> 00:17:44,591
have combined...

292
00:17:45,231 --> 00:17:47,761
and seem to be suppressing
his memory recovery.

293
00:17:48,961 --> 00:17:51,431
He's been neglected like that
for 30 years.

294
00:17:52,471 --> 00:17:54,141
Can he really get better?

295
00:17:54,741 --> 00:17:57,441
Of course. Don't worry
too much, Mother.

296
00:17:57,611 --> 00:18:00,641
According to today's tests,
he doesn't have diabetes...

297
00:18:00,711 --> 00:18:04,181
and there are no major issues,
so that's a relief.

298
00:18:04,981 --> 00:18:07,051
What happened to that woman?
Did they catch her?

299
00:18:07,251 --> 00:18:08,521
She's on the run.

300
00:18:09,251 --> 00:18:12,191
I think Father will have
to be questioned soon too.

301
00:18:13,821 --> 00:18:15,961
Hey, Father's out.

302
00:18:19,661 --> 00:18:20,801
Feel refreshed?

303
00:18:23,101 --> 00:18:26,471
Look at you, Father. All cleaned up.

304
00:18:26,871 --> 00:18:29,501
Right? He looks handsome
like his old self again.

305
00:18:30,111 --> 00:18:32,241
His looks were always just so-so.

306
00:18:32,771 --> 00:18:35,281
- Were they?
- Mom, come on...

307
00:18:36,681 --> 00:18:39,481
Honey, aren't you hungry?

308
00:18:40,051 --> 00:18:41,421
A little.

309
00:18:42,481 --> 00:18:43,891
How about some braised pollack?

310
00:18:44,521 --> 00:18:46,891
You always loved it
with bean sprouts on top.

311
00:18:47,491 --> 00:18:49,161
I do like that.

312
00:18:51,691 --> 00:18:53,761
Hey, Dae Han.
Go buy some bean sprouts.

313
00:18:53,831 --> 00:18:55,461
- Bean sprouts? I'll go get them.
- Yes.

314
00:18:55,531 --> 00:18:57,631
Father, I'll get them.
I'll get the bean sprouts.

315
00:19:01,201 --> 00:19:02,871
Oh my, dust.

316
00:19:08,011 --> 00:19:11,411
Where have you been?
You're supposed to be working.

317
00:19:11,651 --> 00:19:14,351
I was at home.
We found my grandfather.

318
00:19:14,751 --> 00:19:15,851
Oh, you did?

319
00:19:16,351 --> 00:19:17,391
Yes.

320
00:19:18,051 --> 00:19:20,891
That's a relief.
And how is his health?

321
00:19:21,121 --> 00:19:23,991
Other than losing his memory,
he seems to be okay.

322
00:19:27,061 --> 00:19:28,201
Director Yang.

323
00:19:28,631 --> 00:19:32,131
You knew the Fashion Division
would be shut down, didn't you?

324
00:19:32,501 --> 00:19:34,541
That's why you told me
to launch my own brand.

325
00:19:35,001 --> 00:19:36,471
Yes, that's right.

326
00:19:36,671 --> 00:19:40,441
You're always one step ahead,
Director Yang.

327
00:19:40,941 --> 00:19:43,911
It seems you were one step ahead
too, Ms. Kim So Hye.

328
00:19:44,981 --> 00:19:48,721
You knew Park Jun Hyeok
would backstab you?

329
00:19:49,521 --> 00:19:52,651
I thought it was a possibility.

330
00:19:52,951 --> 00:19:55,121
That jerk. I swear...

331
00:19:55,861 --> 00:19:57,291
Just focus on your work.

332
00:19:58,491 --> 00:19:59,631
Where are you going?

333
00:20:00,801 --> 00:20:01,801
To the office.

334
00:20:02,101 --> 00:20:03,271
You have to clean.

335
00:20:04,001 --> 00:20:05,531
- Me?
- Right.

336
00:20:08,171 --> 00:20:09,301
Oh my, dust.

337
00:20:11,111 --> 00:20:15,311
- You had to pick a place like this?
- What's wrong with it?

338
00:20:15,381 --> 00:20:17,881
No deposit and cheap rent.
It's perfect.

339
00:20:19,411 --> 00:20:21,721
I told you I'd give you
as much money as you need.

340
00:20:21,851 --> 00:20:25,021
I'm going to save on operating costs
so I can hire more staff.

341
00:20:26,021 --> 00:20:28,461
How can anyone get inspired
in a place like this?

342
00:20:28,521 --> 00:20:30,461
Maybe not inspiration,
but plenty of perspiration.

343
00:20:30,531 --> 00:20:33,431
Unbelievable. She calls that a joke.

344
00:20:33,761 --> 00:20:36,331
Stop picking a fight and just clean.

345
00:20:36,461 --> 00:20:40,001
I really think we need
to move to a bigger place.

346
00:20:40,071 --> 00:20:41,501
The team is going to grow.

347
00:20:41,571 --> 00:20:44,311
You said you were giving
me authority, didn't you?

348
00:20:44,371 --> 00:20:45,741
Why are you bossing me around?

349
00:20:45,811 --> 00:20:48,881
Full authority?
Only over the design.

350
00:20:48,881 --> 00:20:52,481
- And the workplace is included.
- Oh, you've got to be kidding me.

351
00:20:54,481 --> 00:20:55,781
What will you do
about the furniture?

352
00:20:56,081 --> 00:20:57,321
I'm going to buy it tomorrow.

353
00:20:57,621 --> 00:21:00,791
Okay, fine.
Let's just eat first, all right?

354
00:21:01,861 --> 00:21:03,791
- Sounds good.
- Let's go.

355
00:21:03,861 --> 00:21:06,131
So Hye. Let's just order in.

356
00:21:06,391 --> 00:21:09,201
Go eat by yourself.
Or go home to your parents.

357
00:21:10,631 --> 00:21:14,001
Gosh. Unbelievable.

358
00:21:27,451 --> 00:21:31,191
He always said it was his favorite,
and look how much he's enjoying it.

359
00:21:31,951 --> 00:21:34,321
He said he could eat this
for the rest of his life...

360
00:21:34,321 --> 00:21:35,361
and never get tired of it.

361
00:21:36,421 --> 00:21:39,831
Father, eat slowly
or you might get indigestion.

362
00:21:39,831 --> 00:21:40,901
She's right.

363
00:21:40,901 --> 00:21:42,401
Thank you.

364
00:21:45,801 --> 00:21:46,801
Father.

365
00:21:48,141 --> 00:21:49,401
I'm getting married.

366
00:21:50,211 --> 00:21:51,641
Congratulations.

367
00:21:52,671 --> 00:21:55,541
I'll bring my wife to see you.
You know her too.

368
00:21:58,181 --> 00:22:00,081
The day after tomorrow,
we'll register our marriage...

369
00:22:00,151 --> 00:22:01,321
and spend the night at a hotel.

370
00:22:02,451 --> 00:22:05,251
Dae Han, forget
about household stuff...

371
00:22:05,321 --> 00:22:07,621
and have a wonderful time
with your new bride.

372
00:22:07,691 --> 00:22:10,591
- Right.
- Okay, Seong Mi.

373
00:22:12,531 --> 00:22:14,131
By the way, Father.

374
00:22:14,401 --> 00:22:16,871
That song you used to hear
on the cassette player.

375
00:22:17,171 --> 00:22:19,131
Yeo Jin's
"I Miss You More and More."

376
00:22:19,431 --> 00:22:22,771
That's Mom's favorite song.

377
00:22:23,441 --> 00:22:25,041
Is that so?

378
00:22:27,981 --> 00:22:29,541
Even if you lose your memories,

379
00:22:29,611 --> 00:22:33,211
strong feelings from the past
stay in the subconscious.

380
00:22:33,881 --> 00:22:37,521
Father, you were so
romantic back in the day.

381
00:22:37,751 --> 00:22:39,591
Every morning, you and Mom
would even waltz together.

382
00:22:39,891 --> 00:22:41,861
- That's right.
- You remember, right?

383
00:22:41,921 --> 00:22:42,991
You remember, right?

384
00:22:44,531 --> 00:22:45,791
I'm sorry.

385
00:22:49,801 --> 00:22:52,331
- What? Why?
- Father, what's wrong?

386
00:22:52,871 --> 00:22:54,671
Father, does your head hurt?

387
00:22:55,341 --> 00:22:58,471
My head hurts so much.
I need to rest. I'm sorry.

388
00:22:58,541 --> 00:23:02,211
I'll help you. Be careful.
Slowly, Father.

389
00:23:06,081 --> 00:23:09,581
- Come on in.
- Why does he keep apologizing?

390
00:23:09,781 --> 00:23:11,821
It's an anxiety response
seen in people...

391
00:23:11,891 --> 00:23:13,921
who've been controlled
for a long time.

392
00:23:15,021 --> 00:23:17,131
Did we rush things?

393
00:23:17,791 --> 00:23:21,101
He has 30 years of memories
from living as Jo Mun Sik.

394
00:23:22,031 --> 00:23:24,801
He must be incredibly confused
right now.

395
00:23:32,611 --> 00:23:36,481
So Grandfather really
doesn't remember anything?

396
00:23:36,951 --> 00:23:39,851
Yes. At least we found him.

397
00:23:39,951 --> 00:23:42,751
I was worried we might
never find him.

398
00:23:42,821 --> 00:23:44,391
I was really so worried.

399
00:23:44,851 --> 00:23:47,191
Dong Suk, take good care of him
when you move in too.

400
00:23:47,361 --> 00:23:48,921
Yes, of course.

401
00:23:50,031 --> 00:23:51,791
Auntie, when are you moving?

402
00:23:52,591 --> 00:23:54,661
The day after tomorrow.
He suggested we register...

403
00:23:54,731 --> 00:23:56,161
and spend the night at a hotel
before I move in.

404
00:23:57,771 --> 00:23:59,671
Your wedding night.

405
00:24:00,471 --> 00:24:02,741
Honey, are you okay?

406
00:24:03,201 --> 00:24:05,511
Pardon? Oh, yes.

407
00:24:06,271 --> 00:24:09,241
Min Seo will be fine.

408
00:24:10,281 --> 00:24:12,411
Her flight arrives
early in the morning...

409
00:24:12,481 --> 00:24:14,051
so she'll call tomorrow, Mom.

410
00:24:14,681 --> 00:24:15,681
Okay.

411
00:24:33,841 --> 00:24:34,841
Honey.

412
00:24:35,541 --> 00:24:37,611
To coincide with
Min Seo's school break...

413
00:24:37,911 --> 00:24:39,241
what if we went to the US?

414
00:24:41,281 --> 00:24:44,551
- Really?
- Yes, with Eun Bin.

415
00:24:46,611 --> 00:24:49,851
We could meet
Min Seo's adoptive parents...

416
00:24:50,151 --> 00:24:53,221
and see where and how
our Min Seo grew up.

417
00:24:53,791 --> 00:24:55,521
I thought you'd want to see that.

418
00:24:56,391 --> 00:24:57,691
Honey.

419
00:25:05,701 --> 00:25:09,471
- I can sleep on the floor.
- No.

420
00:25:09,771 --> 00:25:12,211
Don't worry about me.
Sleep comfortably in the bed.

421
00:25:13,411 --> 00:25:16,541
Father's here,
and you're in separate rooms?

422
00:25:17,151 --> 00:25:18,951
Don't be ridiculous.

423
00:25:20,281 --> 00:25:22,251
Are you upset
he doesn't recognize you?

424
00:25:23,891 --> 00:25:25,021
Upset? Of course not.

425
00:25:25,491 --> 00:25:27,391
He's back, and that's
all that matters.

426
00:25:28,391 --> 00:25:32,531
- He'll get better in time.
- I'll do everything I can.

427
00:25:33,661 --> 00:25:36,001
You're sick yourself.
You shouldn't be worrying like this.

428
00:25:36,561 --> 00:25:40,571
I get more energized
when there's a problem to solve.

429
00:25:41,301 --> 00:25:45,171
The DNA test results come
out this week, right?

430
00:25:46,011 --> 00:25:49,341
No matter the results,
I just need the right treatment,

431
00:25:49,411 --> 00:25:51,051
so don't you worry about me either.

432
00:25:51,881 --> 00:25:52,881
Okay.

433
00:25:53,451 --> 00:25:54,521
Okay.

434
00:26:03,891 --> 00:26:06,461
He used to seem so big,

435
00:26:07,031 --> 00:26:08,601
but he looks so small now.

436
00:26:10,871 --> 00:26:15,501
How hard must he have worked?
His hands are callused.

437
00:26:18,341 --> 00:26:19,341
Jeong Han...

438
00:26:19,611 --> 00:26:22,011
- Let's go. We'll wake him.
- Right, okay.

439
00:26:31,491 --> 00:26:33,351
He's so sensitive to
the slightest sound.

440
00:26:34,521 --> 00:26:38,461
He must have lived in constant
fear of being discovered.

441
00:26:38,531 --> 00:26:41,001
But Jeong Han, earlier
at the Police Substation...

442
00:26:41,061 --> 00:26:44,331
Father said, "I killed someone."
What do you think that meant?

443
00:26:45,371 --> 00:26:49,101
I don't know. We'll find out
as we investigate.

444
00:26:49,501 --> 00:26:50,871
You think we can catch that woman?

445
00:26:51,441 --> 00:26:54,611
We have to. We will.

446
00:27:21,801 --> 00:27:23,101
Darn it!

447
00:27:27,641 --> 00:27:30,611
(Onjeong Police Substation)

448
00:27:34,381 --> 00:27:37,521
Do you think Jo Mi Hyang killed
her brother, Jo Mun Sik?

449
00:27:38,191 --> 00:27:39,321
Who knows.

450
00:27:39,521 --> 00:27:43,791
Could Jo Mun Sik's death be
related to Mr. Gong Gi Cheol?

451
00:27:43,931 --> 00:27:45,131
I don't know.

452
00:27:45,691 --> 00:27:48,261
And Jo Mi Hyang has vanished
without a trace, right?

453
00:27:48,861 --> 00:27:51,001
Yes. After Mr. Gong escaped,

454
00:27:51,001 --> 00:27:52,501
she seems to have given up
trying to stow away.

455
00:27:54,571 --> 00:27:56,201
Since Mr. Gong is in poor health,

456
00:27:56,271 --> 00:27:58,271
should we question him
at the hospital?

457
00:27:58,541 --> 00:28:02,941
Yes. And we should let
his family know...

458
00:28:03,141 --> 00:28:05,581
not to leave him alone.

459
00:28:06,151 --> 00:28:07,151
Yes, sir.

460
00:28:08,851 --> 00:28:12,421
Do you think Jo Mi Hyang
will show up in Onjeong again?

461
00:28:13,321 --> 00:28:14,391
Probably.

462
00:28:19,691 --> 00:28:20,831
Mi Hyang!

463
00:28:21,661 --> 00:28:22,761
Mi Hyang!

464
00:28:25,831 --> 00:28:27,241
Get me some water, Mi Hyang.

465
00:28:28,501 --> 00:28:30,811
Father.

466
00:28:34,241 --> 00:28:38,251
Mi Hyang.
Where is my sister, Mi Hyang?

467
00:28:39,751 --> 00:28:44,251
Father, she's not your sister.

468
00:28:45,251 --> 00:28:46,251
What?

469
00:28:46,951 --> 00:28:50,861
Father, you only have
one younger brother. Okay?

470
00:28:53,831 --> 00:28:54,961
Where is this?

471
00:28:56,231 --> 00:28:59,801
This is your house, Father. Okay?

472
00:29:00,901 --> 00:29:02,341
Really?

473
00:29:04,211 --> 00:29:07,181
Father, here. Have some water.

474
00:29:07,541 --> 00:29:09,581
Oh, thank you.

475
00:29:10,611 --> 00:29:13,651
Father, it's me, Jeong Han.

476
00:29:14,081 --> 00:29:16,121
I'm your eldest son.

477
00:29:16,181 --> 00:29:19,151
So you don't have to use
formal language anymore. Okay?

478
00:29:19,691 --> 00:29:20,961
Really?

479
00:29:22,421 --> 00:29:24,961
- Thanks.
- Of course.

480
00:29:26,061 --> 00:29:27,061
Yes.

481
00:29:32,631 --> 00:29:33,971
How's Grandfather?

482
00:29:34,271 --> 00:29:35,941
He looked like he was having
a really hard time.

483
00:29:36,241 --> 00:29:39,311
Everything's unfamiliar,
so he's at a complete loss.

484
00:29:39,671 --> 00:29:43,511
By the way,
is your business going well?

485
00:29:44,451 --> 00:29:46,651
It's a mess
since it's just getting started.

486
00:29:47,381 --> 00:29:49,651
Ju Ah. You came home late
but you're up early.

487
00:29:49,721 --> 00:29:52,491
Yes. Director Yang
is really nagging me.

488
00:29:52,621 --> 00:29:54,421
He's such a thorn in my side.

489
00:29:54,421 --> 00:29:56,591
I think we'll be
at each other's throats soon.

490
00:30:00,231 --> 00:30:03,231
I have to stop somewhere,
so I'm heading out now.

491
00:30:03,301 --> 00:30:04,331
- Grandma, thank you.
- Leaving already?

492
00:30:08,271 --> 00:30:11,671
She'll do fine on her own.
Let's not worry, okay?

493
00:30:12,171 --> 00:30:15,011
We're about to become
a family, after all.

494
00:30:15,111 --> 00:30:16,881
You don't think she'd fall
for him again, do you?

495
00:30:17,351 --> 00:30:19,311
About Gi Cheol.

496
00:30:20,011 --> 00:30:23,321
What if we take him
to our clinic and the pharmacy?

497
00:30:23,521 --> 00:30:25,621
You never know.
It might jog his memory.

498
00:30:26,651 --> 00:30:28,061
That sounds like a good idea.

499
00:30:28,521 --> 00:30:32,531
Stimulating familiar senses
can help with memory recovery.

500
00:30:32,591 --> 00:30:33,591
Right.

501
00:30:37,601 --> 00:30:40,571
Father, when you were watching TV,

502
00:30:40,641 --> 00:30:42,601
did this clinic seem
familiar to you?

503
00:30:43,271 --> 00:30:46,811
Yes. For some reason,
it felt like a place I knew.

504
00:30:47,641 --> 00:30:48,981
It was a really good idea
to go on that show.

505
00:30:50,611 --> 00:30:52,611
But was I really a doctor?

506
00:30:53,011 --> 00:30:54,051
Yes.

507
00:30:54,521 --> 00:30:57,291
You were the second generation,
and I'm the third.

508
00:30:57,421 --> 00:31:00,251
You're the head
of Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic.

509
