515
00:31:32,491 --> 00:31:35,261
<i>You are my personal IV drip</i>
<i>My very own intravenous shot</i>

516
00:31:35,961 --> 00:31:38,731
<i>You're the cure for my arrhythmia</i>

517
00:31:41,061 --> 00:31:43,731
Father, are you all right?

518
00:31:47,471 --> 00:31:51,741
<i>You are my personal IV drip</i>
<i>My very own intravenous shot</i>

519
00:31:52,111 --> 00:31:54,681
Father.

520
00:31:55,141 --> 00:31:57,081
Jeong Han, isn't that
your original song?

521
00:31:57,481 --> 00:31:59,951
It's a song I wrote with Father.

522
00:32:00,411 --> 00:32:02,621
Do you remember that song?

523
00:32:03,281 --> 00:32:05,851
- Yes.
- Jeong Han!

524
00:32:05,921 --> 00:32:08,991
Hey. No, Father,
what about other things?

525
00:32:09,091 --> 00:32:10,831
Do you remember anything else?

526
00:32:11,631 --> 00:32:13,531
I was playing the guitar.

527
00:32:13,691 --> 00:32:17,671
That's right. You taught me
how to play the guitar, Father.

528
00:32:19,001 --> 00:32:20,131
Jeong Han!

529
00:32:20,471 --> 00:32:23,241
- Father.
- Father will recover in no time.

530
00:32:23,401 --> 00:32:25,171
Do you really remember?

531
00:32:28,711 --> 00:32:32,081
- Mom.
- Has he seen the clinic?

532
00:32:32,181 --> 00:32:35,621
- Yes.
- Mom, Father remembers the song.

533
00:32:35,751 --> 00:32:38,351
- Yes.
- A song?

534
00:32:38,491 --> 00:32:40,791
<i>- You are</i>
<i>- My personal IV drip</i>

535
00:32:40,791 --> 00:32:43,091
<i>My very own intravenous shot</i>

536
00:32:43,221 --> 00:32:46,461
<i>- You're the cure for my arrhythmia</i>
<i>- You're the cure for my arrhythmia</i>

537
00:32:46,761 --> 00:32:48,801
<i>- You are my IV drip</i>
<i>- You are my IV drip</i>

538
00:32:48,801 --> 00:32:51,131
<i>- My personal Band-Aid</i>
<i>- My personal Band-Aid</i>

539
00:32:51,371 --> 00:32:55,741
<i>- You heal all my wounds</i>
<i>- You heal all my wounds</i>

540
00:32:55,741 --> 00:32:57,271
<i>- Thump thump</i>
<i>- Thump thump</i>

541
00:32:58,171 --> 00:33:00,811
This is the song you wrote
when you proposed to Seong Mi.

542
00:33:00,941 --> 00:33:03,881
That's right, Mom.
Father and Jeong Han wrote it.

543
00:33:06,711 --> 00:33:09,921
Father, do you happen
to remember this place?

544
00:33:10,381 --> 00:33:12,321
Whenever you had a free moment,
you'd come here...

545
00:33:12,621 --> 00:33:14,691
and keep Mom company. Remember?

546
00:33:17,361 --> 00:33:18,461
I'm sorry.

547
00:33:19,191 --> 00:33:20,861
It's okay.

548
00:33:21,531 --> 00:33:22,701
Take your time.

549
00:33:23,431 --> 00:33:25,131
And please, don't...

550
00:33:25,671 --> 00:33:28,241
say you're sorry anymore.

551
00:33:32,271 --> 00:33:33,571
- Oh.
- Yes, you're here?

552
00:33:34,081 --> 00:33:35,241
You're here, sir?

553
00:33:35,941 --> 00:33:39,781
- I'm your father-in-law.
- Yes, Father-in-law.

554
00:33:40,781 --> 00:33:43,021
But, sir, what is that?

555
00:33:44,321 --> 00:33:46,191
Take this. It's Memory Tonic.

556
00:33:46,521 --> 00:33:48,461
I had it made with the finest herbs.

557
00:33:49,621 --> 00:33:50,631
Thanks.

558
00:33:51,691 --> 00:33:52,891
Why are you being so casual again?

559
00:33:53,731 --> 00:33:55,931
- You said we were friends.
- Look at this guy.

560
00:34:12,811 --> 00:34:15,851
Hey, this is attempted murder.

561
00:34:15,921 --> 00:34:18,651
Too bad it was just an attempt.
I was trying to kill you.

562
00:34:19,991 --> 00:34:21,921
Hey, take it easy.

563
00:34:22,491 --> 00:34:24,461
Hey, how could you do this?

564
00:34:24,761 --> 00:34:29,201
We went through so much to save FG.
And you sold it off just like that?

565
00:34:29,531 --> 00:34:31,201
You're lower than a worm.

566
00:34:31,831 --> 00:34:33,271
How could you take
our Fashion Division...

567
00:34:33,331 --> 00:34:37,311
our colleagues, and throw them
out on the street overnight?

568
00:34:37,641 --> 00:34:39,011
And you call yourself a human being?

569
00:34:39,411 --> 00:34:40,511
Seriously.

570
00:34:40,981 --> 00:34:43,681
I had no choice.
It was for the company.

571
00:34:44,381 --> 00:34:46,351
Don't make me laugh.
This is unbelievable.

572
00:34:46,611 --> 00:34:49,121
Since when did you become
such a slave to greed?

573
00:34:49,381 --> 00:34:51,021
Seriously, people are watching.

574
00:34:51,621 --> 00:34:53,251
Do you know how expensive
this suit is?

575
00:34:53,351 --> 00:34:55,791
Like I care?
It looks ridiculous on you.

576
00:34:55,921 --> 00:34:57,121
No way.

577
00:34:57,361 --> 00:35:00,831
From now on,
you're not my friend. Got it?

578
00:35:01,131 --> 00:35:04,771
I'm not friends with vermin.
I ought to just...

579
00:35:06,601 --> 00:35:07,971
Hurry up. What are you doing?

580
00:35:21,051 --> 00:35:22,051
Well...

581
00:35:22,521 --> 00:35:24,591
I told you we should buy
some decent furniture.

582
00:35:24,851 --> 00:35:26,291
Why a secondhand store?

583
00:35:26,621 --> 00:35:29,391
New things become used
the moment you use them.

584
00:35:29,661 --> 00:35:31,191
We haven't secured
any investors yet.

585
00:35:31,191 --> 00:35:32,731
We have to save every penny.

586
00:35:32,961 --> 00:35:35,301
I'll take care of the funding.

587
00:35:37,131 --> 00:35:38,431
How are you going to do that?

588
00:35:38,501 --> 00:35:40,871
By selling your house and car
and taking out a loan?

589
00:35:41,101 --> 00:35:42,101
I'll have to.

590
00:35:42,871 --> 00:35:44,771
You're surprisingly out of touch.

591
00:35:51,081 --> 00:35:52,081
Wow.

592
00:35:54,521 --> 00:35:57,521
- Let's buy this, okay?
- It takes up too much space.

593
00:35:59,221 --> 00:36:01,361
Oh, what about this table then?

594
00:36:01,761 --> 00:36:03,691
I think it'd be great
for a coffee machine.

595
00:36:03,991 --> 00:36:05,731
We'll be drinking instant coffee.

596
00:36:08,731 --> 00:36:10,501
If you were going to
say no to everything,

597
00:36:10,561 --> 00:36:11,701
why did you bring me along?

598
00:36:13,431 --> 00:36:14,801
You have to pay.

599
00:36:16,901 --> 00:36:17,911
Fine.

600
00:36:18,911 --> 00:36:21,281
Use this to pay,
and attach the receipt.

601
00:36:22,481 --> 00:36:25,081
You need to register the business...

602
00:36:25,151 --> 00:36:26,651
so decide on a brand name
by the end of the day.

603
00:36:27,111 --> 00:36:28,121
Where are you going?

604
00:36:28,621 --> 00:36:30,921
We still have to clean
and set up the furniture.

605
00:36:31,121 --> 00:36:33,591
Handle it yourself. I'm off, then.

606
00:36:36,321 --> 00:36:39,091
When did he become such a jerk?

607
00:36:39,491 --> 00:36:41,661
If you'll act like this,
you should've hired more people.

608
00:36:43,331 --> 00:36:46,031
Unbelievable. Gosh.

609
00:37:29,481 --> 00:37:30,711
Welcome, little brother.

610
00:37:35,181 --> 00:37:37,991
I was so happy
to finally have family.

611
00:37:41,661 --> 00:37:42,791
How could he do this?

612
00:37:44,891 --> 00:37:45,991
How...

613
00:38:05,581 --> 00:38:06,581
So Hye.

614
00:38:07,351 --> 00:38:11,391
This is the first design book
I ever made. Could you take a look?

615
00:38:13,921 --> 00:38:15,521
(Pink Collared Shirt,
Khaki Cargo Shorts, Ripstop Fabric)

616
00:38:17,261 --> 00:38:18,991
It's sporty casualwear.

617
00:38:19,531 --> 00:38:22,401
It's very modern and stylish.

618
00:38:24,131 --> 00:38:27,101
If I ever launch my own brand...

619
00:38:27,171 --> 00:38:28,741
this is the style
I always wanted to create.

620
00:38:29,371 --> 00:38:31,571
Have you come up with a brand name?

621
00:38:32,411 --> 00:38:33,411
Pelliv.

622
00:38:33,811 --> 00:38:35,741
It means something like
the happiness...

623
00:38:35,811 --> 00:38:37,541
that comes alive when you wear it.

624
00:38:38,351 --> 00:38:40,181
- What do you think?
- I love it.

625
00:38:40,181 --> 00:38:41,881
I can feel the brand mood
right away.

626
00:38:42,281 --> 00:38:46,851
Okay, we don't have time
for a full collection.

627
00:38:46,921 --> 00:38:48,321
Let's minimize the number of styles.

628
00:38:48,621 --> 00:38:49,661
Got it.

629
00:38:51,091 --> 00:38:52,231
Okay.

630
00:38:52,591 --> 00:38:53,591
Is anyone here?

631
00:38:54,031 --> 00:38:55,031
Come in.

632
00:39:08,311 --> 00:39:09,311
Right.

633
00:39:09,911 --> 00:39:11,111
- Hey.
- Oh my.

634
00:39:11,211 --> 00:39:12,211
Relax, man.

635
00:39:12,581 --> 00:39:14,681
I'm so nervous.

636
00:39:15,321 --> 00:39:16,921
I'm glad Gi Cheol is getting better.

637
00:39:17,651 --> 00:39:20,821
Dr. Gong here used
to adore Dong Suk.

638
00:39:21,221 --> 00:39:22,461
You remember.

639
00:39:24,291 --> 00:39:25,391
He said he had no daughter...

640
00:39:25,461 --> 00:39:26,961
so he'd always hold her hand
when they went out.

641
00:39:28,901 --> 00:39:29,901
Wear this.

642
00:39:30,501 --> 00:39:31,501
It's a watch.

643
00:39:32,201 --> 00:39:35,201
I thought we agreed
to skip the gifts.

644
00:39:35,641 --> 00:39:37,471
I'm giving it to you
to get on your good side.

645
00:39:38,011 --> 00:39:39,011
Take it.

646
00:39:40,241 --> 00:39:41,341
Thank you so much.

647
00:39:42,611 --> 00:39:45,851
As you know,
Dong Suk has been through a lot.

648
00:39:46,781 --> 00:39:49,021
She's had a hard life
after her mother disappeared.

649
00:39:49,881 --> 00:39:52,291
I was hard on her,
saying she was just like her mother.

650
00:39:53,991 --> 00:39:55,161
I'll take good care of her.

651
00:39:56,121 --> 00:40:00,391
Be kind to her, and cherish her.

652
00:40:01,801 --> 00:40:03,561
Thank you for trusting me.

653
00:40:04,131 --> 00:40:05,131
Dong Ik.

654
00:40:05,801 --> 00:40:08,671
I'll be a husband and father
Dong Suk and Ji Hu can be proud of.

655
00:40:11,071 --> 00:40:12,071
Hey, sit comfortably.

656
00:40:13,541 --> 00:40:15,341
Right, thank you.

657
00:40:16,741 --> 00:40:17,781
Dong Suk, this is for you.

658
00:40:18,211 --> 00:40:20,651
You've already given
me so many things.

659
00:40:21,021 --> 00:40:22,251
And there's more?

660
00:40:23,521 --> 00:40:24,751
It's lingerie.

661
00:40:25,821 --> 00:40:28,461
Wear it on your wedding night.
It's really sexy.

662
00:40:29,491 --> 00:40:30,991
Oh my, Se Ri.

663
00:40:31,691 --> 00:40:32,691
Thank you.

664
00:40:34,661 --> 00:40:37,031
I'm going to miss you so much.

665
00:40:37,361 --> 00:40:40,931
Why are you sad your sister-in-law
is getting married?

666
00:40:42,871 --> 00:40:46,071
What is it? Is it because of Ji Hu?

667
00:40:47,011 --> 00:40:49,211
What can I do?
He's being so stubborn.

668
00:40:50,281 --> 00:40:51,551
I feel bad leaving him behind.

669
00:40:51,911 --> 00:40:55,021
With Min Seo gone
and you leaving too,

670
00:40:55,121 --> 00:40:57,321
what will I do if Ji Hu leaves too?

671
00:40:58,451 --> 00:41:00,451
Thank you for saying that, Se Ri.

672
00:41:02,021 --> 00:41:04,791
If you're ever having
a hard time in life,

673
00:41:05,261 --> 00:41:09,131
you have to tell me.
I'm like your real sister.

674
00:41:10,461 --> 00:41:14,771
Se Ri, you're going to make me cry.

675
00:41:16,171 --> 00:41:17,171
Always...

676
00:41:18,541 --> 00:41:20,811
Live a happy and confident life,
Dong Suk.

677
00:41:21,511 --> 00:41:22,511
Okay?

678
00:41:24,751 --> 00:41:25,811
You too, Se Ri.

679
00:41:26,981 --> 00:41:28,751
Take care of my brother...

680
00:41:29,451 --> 00:41:31,621
and please look after
Ji Hu and our father.

681
00:41:33,821 --> 00:41:34,821
I will.

682
00:41:35,621 --> 00:41:38,361
I'm really so sad.

683
00:41:41,531 --> 00:41:42,531
Well...

684
00:41:42,661 --> 00:41:44,601
I should be going now.

685
00:41:45,101 --> 00:41:46,231
You're not drunk, are you?

686
00:41:46,731 --> 00:41:49,301
Of course not.
I'm fine, Father-in-law.

687
00:41:50,641 --> 00:41:53,041
Sleep well, both of you.
See you tomorrow, okay?

688
00:41:54,441 --> 00:41:56,041
You're both so beautiful.

689
00:41:57,681 --> 00:42:00,281
You're drunk. You have
your wedding night tomorrow.

690
00:42:00,351 --> 00:42:04,021
- Goodness, Ji Hu.
- What, Mom? I'm all grown up.

691
00:42:05,191 --> 00:42:08,621
Thank you so much
for packing all this for us.

692
00:42:09,021 --> 00:42:12,531
She spent all day making this.
Enjoy it.

693
00:42:12,761 --> 00:42:16,961
That's a bribe. Take good care
of our Dong Suk.

694
00:42:17,201 --> 00:42:18,201
Yes.

695
00:42:18,831 --> 00:42:19,871
You don't have to worry.

696
00:42:22,941 --> 00:42:24,041
Are you okay?

697
00:42:32,311 --> 00:42:34,821
This is my last night with my son.

698
00:42:35,681 --> 00:42:37,851
I know. I'm so excited.

699
00:42:38,091 --> 00:42:40,851
- You're excited?
- Yes. I get the room to myself.

700
00:42:40,991 --> 00:42:41,991
My gosh.

701
00:42:42,721 --> 00:42:44,931
Mom, I was thinking.

702
00:42:45,261 --> 00:42:46,961
The first time is always
the hardest.

703
00:42:47,731 --> 00:42:50,661
- And?
- But this is your second time.

704
00:42:51,631 --> 00:42:54,371
So this marriage
will definitely be a success.

705
00:42:59,171 --> 00:43:00,171
My son.

706
00:43:01,941 --> 00:43:03,981
You know I love you
very much, right?

707
00:43:04,751 --> 00:43:05,751
I know.

708
00:43:07,211 --> 00:43:09,551
Don't forget your promise
that we'll meet every day.

709
00:43:09,951 --> 00:43:10,951
Promise me.

710
00:43:17,121 --> 00:43:20,331
I think Dae Han had
too much to drink and passed out.

711
00:43:20,661 --> 00:43:24,231
Dong Suk sent over all this food.
What should we do?

712
00:43:25,001 --> 00:43:26,201
I'll take care of it.

713
00:43:26,571 --> 00:43:29,201
Father and my husband
are late, aren't they?

714
00:43:29,271 --> 00:43:31,411
Yes. They said they're taking
a walk around the neighborhood.

715
00:43:31,811 --> 00:43:32,811
That's nice.

716
00:43:33,141 --> 00:43:35,381
Experiencing familiar smells
and sounds...

717
00:43:35,441 --> 00:43:37,611
is good for memory recovery.

718
00:43:38,451 --> 00:43:40,981
Fortunately, he seems
to be adapting quickly.

719
00:43:41,381 --> 00:43:44,021
- Mom, I'm back with Father.
- Oh, yes.

720
00:43:45,521 --> 00:43:47,851
- Did you have a nice walk?
- Yes.

721
00:43:47,991 --> 00:43:50,621
You don't have to be
so formal with me.

722
00:43:52,461 --> 00:43:56,001
He even greeted the neighbors
on his walk today.

723
00:43:56,261 --> 00:43:59,801
Good.
Your uncle is coming this weekend.

724
00:44:01,341 --> 00:44:03,101
Your younger brother is coming.

725
00:44:03,401 --> 00:44:04,401
My brother?

726
00:44:05,141 --> 00:44:06,141
Yes.

727
00:44:06,941 --> 00:44:09,541
- Go in and rest.
- Yes.

728
00:44:10,511 --> 00:44:13,581
- Go ahead, Father.
- Get some rest, Father.

729
00:44:14,511 --> 00:44:16,321
Father.

730
00:44:18,851 --> 00:44:21,121
Did Father just go
into Mother's room?

731
00:44:21,591 --> 00:44:23,021
Looks like it. What do we do?

732
00:44:23,561 --> 00:44:25,231
There's only one bed in there.

733
00:44:26,391 --> 00:44:27,391
Oh, man...

734
00:44:36,371 --> 00:44:39,571
Until your memory comes back...

735
00:44:40,441 --> 00:44:42,511
wouldn't it be more comfortable
if we slept separately?

736
00:44:45,511 --> 00:44:46,551
It's not that.

737
00:44:48,581 --> 00:44:52,421
Why? Is there something
you want to say?

738
00:44:53,491 --> 00:44:54,491
Well, it's just...

739
00:44:56,261 --> 00:44:57,261
I'm sorry.

740
00:44:58,361 --> 00:44:59,361
Pardon?

741
00:45:00,731 --> 00:45:03,561
I may not remember,

742
00:45:04,601 --> 00:45:06,731
but 30 years without a husband,

743
00:45:07,501 --> 00:45:09,141
you must have had such a hard time.

744
00:45:12,141 --> 00:45:14,171
I'll spend the rest of my life
making it up to you.

745
00:45:32,561 --> 00:45:36,761
I've been trying my best to show
a wide variety of products...

746
00:45:37,001 --> 00:45:39,431
and explain all the options
in great detail...

747
00:45:39,701 --> 00:45:43,041
but it doesn't often lead
to an actual sale.

748
00:45:45,511 --> 00:45:46,911
If there are too many options...

749
00:45:46,971 --> 00:45:48,941
some people actually find it
overwhelming.

750
00:45:49,781 --> 00:45:51,481
Try narrowing it down
and recommending...

751
00:45:51,551 --> 00:45:53,981
two or three products
that fit their tastes and budget.

752
00:45:54,381 --> 00:45:57,181
So, the customer's needs...

753
00:45:57,481 --> 00:45:59,951
The most important thing is
to clearly understand them, then?

754
00:46:00,091 --> 00:46:03,461
Right. And as you help them
try things out at their leisure...

755
00:46:03,691 --> 00:46:07,331
it's also good to mention tips
for actual use and customer reviews.

756
00:46:07,591 --> 00:46:10,561
Oh. From customers
who actually bought them...

757
00:46:10,701 --> 00:46:12,731
Are you talking about their
reactions and things like that?

758
00:46:12,871 --> 00:46:15,641
Yes. You're such a quick study...

759
00:46:16,001 --> 00:46:17,401
I'm sure you'll be great
at this in no time.

760
00:46:20,841 --> 00:46:21,841
You made it safely.

761
00:46:22,441 --> 00:46:24,641
Have you eaten? Right.

762
00:46:25,311 --> 00:46:28,421
- Honey.
- Mom's here. Just a second.

763
00:46:29,981 --> 00:46:31,591
- Mom.
- Oh, Min Seo.

764
00:46:32,621 --> 00:46:34,091
Did you get to the US okay?

765
00:46:34,291 --> 00:46:36,821
Yes. I'm still not used
to the time difference,

766
00:46:36,891 --> 00:46:39,191
so I've been groggy,
but I'm finally awake.

767
00:46:39,661 --> 00:46:40,661
I see.

768
00:46:41,361 --> 00:46:44,531
- It's nighttime there, isn't it?
- Yes.

769
00:46:44,801 --> 00:46:48,271
It's too late now. I'll show you
my neighborhood tomorrow.

770
00:46:48,901 --> 00:46:51,741
Okay. You must be tired.
Get some rest.

771
00:46:52,211 --> 00:46:56,311
Okay. Thanks for putting Mom on,
Stepdad.

772
00:46:57,081 --> 00:47:00,851
Min Seo, let's talk again soon. Bye.

773
00:47:01,921 --> 00:47:03,251
(3H Acupressure Bed)

774
00:47:03,351 --> 00:47:04,621
How did you manage to find
the time to come?

775
00:47:05,551 --> 00:47:07,291
There were hardly any appointments
this afternoon...

776
00:47:07,891 --> 00:47:10,321
so Father said he'd see
the patients himself.

777
00:47:10,991 --> 00:47:12,231
Let's go to lunch.

778
00:47:12,561 --> 00:47:15,531
I made a reservation
at a nice restaurant.

779
00:47:33,251 --> 00:47:34,281
Hi, Jason.

780
00:47:35,121 --> 00:47:36,451
Yes, I'm free tomorrow.

781
00:47:37,421 --> 00:47:39,791
Oh, okay. I'll see you there then.

782
00:47:42,461 --> 00:47:43,461
Oh my gosh.

783
00:47:44,261 --> 00:47:46,491
What? What are you doing here?

784
00:47:47,191 --> 00:47:50,561
- I'm here for tutoring.
- What? Ji Hu's still at school.

785
00:47:51,061 --> 00:47:53,331
I helped my uncle
with his proposal...

786
00:47:53,401 --> 00:47:54,401
and came early to get ready.

787
00:47:55,101 --> 00:47:56,701
Ji Hu's room is over there.

788
00:48:01,681 --> 00:48:03,811
Hey, why are you covering your face?

789
00:48:04,241 --> 00:48:06,081
Because I'm not wearing any makeup.

790
00:48:08,011 --> 00:48:09,721
I've known you
since you had a runny nose.

791
00:48:10,021 --> 00:48:11,021
Why are you so shy all of a sudden?

792
00:48:12,451 --> 00:48:14,191
You're prettier
without makeup anyway.

793
00:48:19,831 --> 00:48:21,931
Gosh. So sweet.

794
00:48:32,811 --> 00:48:34,641
(Will you marry me?)

795
00:48:37,011 --> 00:48:38,011
(Will you marry me?)

796
00:48:38,011 --> 00:48:40,481
When did you do all this?

797
00:48:42,421 --> 00:48:43,421
Before we went
to the district office.

798
00:48:43,681 --> 00:48:45,291
Woo Jae and I came early
to set it up.

799
00:48:46,191 --> 00:48:48,151
But I didn't prepare anything.

800
00:48:48,421 --> 00:48:51,421
It's okay. I took care of it.
Dolphin, by the way,

801
00:48:52,161 --> 00:48:54,931
this isn't my first time,
but why am I so nervous?

802
00:48:55,401 --> 00:48:58,001
But it is your first.
For us, this is the first time.

803
00:48:58,701 --> 00:48:59,701
You're right.

804
00:49:05,311 --> 00:49:06,741
Yes. First...

805
00:49:07,111 --> 00:49:10,011
to all our guests who joined us
for our wedding...

806
00:49:10,941 --> 00:49:13,311
we'd like to express
our sincere gratitude.

807
00:49:13,651 --> 00:49:15,521
Ready. Bow.

808
00:49:16,521 --> 00:49:17,521
Thank you.

809
00:49:21,151 --> 00:49:22,161
Everyone's smiling.

810
00:49:22,961 --> 00:49:24,721
Well then...

811
00:49:25,091 --> 00:49:27,461
we will now begin
our wedding ceremony.

812
00:49:29,401 --> 00:49:30,401
Stand like this.

813
00:49:46,081 --> 00:49:47,081
Let me.

814
00:49:52,221 --> 00:49:53,221
Oh, right.

815
00:49:58,661 --> 00:49:59,661
Our wedding vows.

816
00:50:00,631 --> 00:50:01,901
I, the groom, Gong Dae Han,

817
00:50:02,331 --> 00:50:05,431
take Yang Dong Suk, my life's
endorphin, as my bride.

818
00:50:10,901 --> 00:50:12,971
Until our hair turns gray...

819
00:50:13,871 --> 00:50:14,871
as a lover...

820
00:50:16,341 --> 00:50:17,741
a best friend...

821
00:50:19,051 --> 00:50:20,351
and a dependable husband...

822
00:50:21,951 --> 00:50:23,381
I will be with her forever.

823
00:50:26,021 --> 00:50:27,121
I swear.

824
00:50:31,561 --> 00:50:33,761
- I'll do it too.
- Okay.

825
00:50:34,091 --> 00:50:35,561
I, Yang Dong Suk,

826
00:50:36,061 --> 00:50:39,631
take Gong Dae Han, the vitamin
of my life, as my groom.

827
00:50:40,571 --> 00:50:43,041
I will love him
for the rest of my life...

828
00:50:43,401 --> 00:50:45,041
and live happily with him.

829
00:50:47,271 --> 00:50:49,211
- Really?
- I mean it.

830
00:50:58,651 --> 00:51:02,691
You even got rings? But wait,
how did you know my size?

831
00:51:03,261 --> 00:51:04,291
Ji Hu...

832
00:51:05,391 --> 00:51:07,491
He measured your finger
when you were asleep.

833
00:51:07,491 --> 00:51:08,601
Isn't it beautiful?

834
00:51:37,221 --> 00:51:38,431
In the presence of everyone here...

835
00:51:38,831 --> 00:51:41,931
and with the blessings
of our guests,

836
00:51:43,131 --> 00:51:45,771
we now declare that we have become
husband and wife.

837
00:51:50,141 --> 00:51:51,141
The groom...

838
00:51:52,511 --> 00:51:53,611
may now kiss...

839
00:51:54,841 --> 00:51:56,011
the bride.

840
00:52:08,351 --> 00:52:09,361
I love you.

841
00:52:10,191 --> 00:52:11,191
Me too.

842
00:52:24,871 --> 00:52:25,911
I'm leaving.

843
00:52:29,511 --> 00:52:31,981
Hey, aren't you even
going to say goodbye?

844
00:52:32,211 --> 00:52:36,951
You're not my old crush anymore.
You're my in-law. Goodbye.

845
00:52:39,421 --> 00:52:40,621
What's wrong?

846
00:52:41,351 --> 00:52:42,991
If something's bothering you,
you can tell me.

847
00:52:46,831 --> 00:52:50,661
- Fine, I'm leaving then.
- Well...

848
00:52:52,071 --> 00:52:55,841
Jason said my channel has
nothing memorable.

849
00:52:55,901 --> 00:52:58,241
He told me to show
something truly entertaining...

850
00:52:59,241 --> 00:53:00,541
but I'm drawing a blank.

851
00:53:01,611 --> 00:53:03,711
Why did you want to be
a YouTuber in the first place?

852
00:53:04,011 --> 00:53:08,351
I started it to become successful
and support you.

853
00:53:09,121 --> 00:53:12,021
- Still?
- No, absolutely not, in-law.

854
00:53:14,251 --> 00:53:15,521
So you're trying something,

855
00:53:15,591 --> 00:53:17,021
without knowing why you want to.

856
00:53:18,291 --> 00:53:20,031
I guess so.

857
00:53:20,361 --> 00:53:23,831
I think you need to go back
and figure out your career path.

858
00:53:24,361 --> 00:53:25,371
How?

859
00:53:27,271 --> 00:53:28,601
What do you enjoy doing the most?

860
00:53:30,801 --> 00:53:33,441
When I'm styling people.

861
00:53:33,611 --> 00:53:38,311
Like my aunt, my mom, or my friends.
They love it when I style them.

862
00:53:38,651 --> 00:53:39,711
I'm good at it.

863
00:53:40,011 --> 00:53:41,951
Then get some styling experience.

864
00:53:42,021 --> 00:53:44,981
Not just with family,
but out in the real world.

865
00:53:45,451 --> 00:53:48,091
- In the real world?
- Yes.

866
00:53:48,961 --> 00:53:51,221
- I'm off.
- Oh, okay.

867
00:53:56,761 --> 00:53:59,271
No way. Get a grip, Eun Bin.

868
00:53:59,831 --> 00:54:00,831
No.

869
00:54:01,371 --> 00:54:02,471
He's my in-law.

870
00:54:07,071 --> 00:54:10,541
Seriously, what is
everyone thinking?

871
00:54:10,811 --> 00:54:14,011
- Is this a joke?
- No, it's not a joke.

872
00:54:14,411 --> 00:54:17,551
We received a formal offer
from Director Yang.

873
00:54:18,221 --> 00:54:21,021
That's right. We interviewed
with other companies...

874
00:54:21,121 --> 00:54:22,991
and thought carefully
before deciding.

875
00:54:23,461 --> 00:54:25,491
What did Director Yang say
to lure you away?

876
00:54:28,861 --> 00:54:30,601
CEO Gong's brand
will be the spark...

877
00:54:30,661 --> 00:54:33,201
that revives
Taehan Group's Fashion Division.

878
00:54:34,771 --> 00:54:36,671
You all need to be the firewood...

879
00:54:36,741 --> 00:54:38,811
to turn that spark
into a blazing fire.

880
00:54:45,081 --> 00:54:47,181
And you fell for that?

881
00:54:47,451 --> 00:54:48,681
It's romantic, isn't it?

882
00:54:49,981 --> 00:54:53,221
With your experience, you could
work for a big company...

883
00:54:53,291 --> 00:54:54,721
with all the resources you need.

884
00:54:54,921 --> 00:54:58,691
Then Ms. Gong, I mean CEO Gong,
why didn't you go to Harben?

885
00:54:59,031 --> 00:55:00,331
Even if conditions are rough,

886
00:55:00,391 --> 00:55:03,061
isn't it because you wanted
work that makes your heart pound?

887
00:55:05,831 --> 00:55:08,901
We feel the same way,
so be happy to have us.

888
00:55:10,001 --> 00:55:12,811
Anyway, it's great
we're all together again.

889
00:55:13,511 --> 00:55:15,581
Should we order some food?

890
00:55:16,041 --> 00:55:17,041
- Sounds good.
- Yes.

891
00:55:17,441 --> 00:55:19,481
- I'm starving.
- I'm hungry.

892
00:55:19,981 --> 00:55:22,181
- What should we get?
- Well...

893
00:55:22,251 --> 00:55:25,021
How does he plan to raise the funds?

894
00:55:28,221 --> 00:55:29,461
Day drinking?

895
00:55:30,291 --> 00:55:31,821
What, are you giving up
on everything?

896
00:55:32,531 --> 00:55:34,361
I'm taking a vacation for a while.

897
00:55:35,191 --> 00:55:36,461
I can't go to work.

898
00:55:36,861 --> 00:55:38,801
Is that right?
Then give me the money.

899
00:55:40,501 --> 00:55:43,141
- Give you what?
- Money.

900
00:55:43,501 --> 00:55:44,571
Money.

901
00:55:45,611 --> 00:55:46,811
How much?

902
00:55:51,281 --> 00:55:52,281
Read this.

903
00:55:55,151 --> 00:55:57,551
(Designer Brand Launch Proposal)

904
00:55:58,951 --> 00:56:00,151
This is your alternative?

905
00:56:00,351 --> 00:56:02,261
FG may have been sold off,

906
00:56:02,321 --> 00:56:04,161
but Taehan Fashion Division's
spirit lives on.

907
00:56:04,791 --> 00:56:06,031
Explain it in a way
I can understand.

908
00:56:06,161 --> 00:56:09,301
You don't need to know.
Just drink. I'm leaving.

909
00:56:31,481 --> 00:56:32,851
What are you talking about?

910
00:56:33,221 --> 00:56:34,591
You want me to transfer
Director Yang...

911
00:56:34,651 --> 00:56:35,791
to the Strategic Planning Division?

912
00:56:36,221 --> 00:56:40,031
Director Yang will be
an invaluable ally to you.

913
00:56:41,461 --> 00:56:43,201
You said you'd handle him,

914
00:56:43,501 --> 00:56:44,761
and you made him an ally?

915
00:56:45,231 --> 00:56:46,231
Yes, sir.

916
00:56:50,241 --> 00:56:51,641
I don't trust him.

917
00:56:52,241 --> 00:56:53,341
Take it or leave it.

918
00:56:54,111 --> 00:56:55,111
Hey!

919
00:56:55,171 --> 00:56:56,281
(Taehan Group)

920
00:56:57,781 --> 00:56:59,451
Why are you so disrespectful?

921
00:57:02,921 --> 00:57:03,921
Right after my father passed,

922
00:57:03,981 --> 00:57:04,981
we went after
our founding business...

923
00:57:05,021 --> 00:57:06,991
and liquidated the Fashion Division.

924
00:57:07,091 --> 00:57:09,191
Our Group's image took a major hit.

925
00:57:09,761 --> 00:57:11,921
The Group desperately needs
rebranding.

926
00:57:16,231 --> 00:57:17,531
I said, take it or leave it.

927
00:57:18,101 --> 00:57:21,201
Fine. Do it.
I'm telling you to do it.

928
00:57:25,511 --> 00:57:26,511
Yes, sir.

929
00:57:30,411 --> 00:57:32,211
(Director Baek Won Gyu)

930
00:57:32,311 --> 00:57:33,711
Leaving without a single word?

931
00:57:34,481 --> 00:57:35,821
Such an insolent punk.

932
00:57:39,451 --> 00:57:41,421
It's because he's spent time abroad.

933
00:57:43,761 --> 00:57:45,491
What is it? What's your angle?

934
00:57:46,691 --> 00:57:49,601
As you know, he's a total lunatic.

935
00:57:50,031 --> 00:57:52,631
If we just cast him aside,
he'll become uncontrollable.

936
00:57:54,571 --> 00:57:57,371
So you're saying it's better
to keep him close and watch him?

937
00:57:58,971 --> 00:58:00,111
It's safer that way.

938
00:58:06,751 --> 00:58:08,821
Maybe we should have
brought Father with us.

939
00:58:11,021 --> 00:58:12,151
It's fine.

940
00:58:12,691 --> 00:58:16,891
He's not picky.
He wore whatever I bought him.

941
00:58:17,691 --> 00:58:19,631
To think the day would come
when I'd be shopping...

942
00:58:19,691 --> 00:58:21,231
for Father's clothes
with you, Mother...

943
00:58:21,661 --> 00:58:23,101
it feels a little strange.

944
00:58:23,461 --> 00:58:24,461
It is, isn't it?

945
00:58:28,131 --> 00:58:29,141
This one.

946
00:58:30,041 --> 00:58:31,041
How about this one?

947
00:58:31,171 --> 00:58:34,571
It's simple and nice.
It would look great on Father.

948
00:58:34,741 --> 00:58:37,911
Let's get this one.
Now let's look for pants.

949
00:58:39,081 --> 00:58:40,451
What style are you looking for?

950
00:58:40,511 --> 00:58:44,521
Something light and comfortable,
please.

951
00:58:44,821 --> 00:58:48,291
- Then how about these ones?
- Okay.

952
00:58:50,191 --> 00:58:51,191
Here you are.

953
00:58:51,591 --> 00:58:54,591
The colors are elegant,
so they're popular gifts.

954
00:58:54,731 --> 00:58:56,561
- They are.
- Like this.

955
00:58:56,631 --> 00:58:59,371
They go together nicely.

956
00:59:00,271 --> 00:59:04,271
Seeing Father all dressed up
will make me so proud.

957
00:59:04,871 --> 00:59:05,871
I know.

958
00:59:07,811 --> 00:59:10,181
Will the investigation take long?

959
00:59:10,441 --> 00:59:12,111
It's just the initial
witness interview.

960
00:59:12,181 --> 00:59:13,951
We'll only ask
a few questions for now.

961
00:59:14,181 --> 00:59:15,411
You don't need to worry.

962
00:59:16,421 --> 00:59:18,991
But my father...

963
00:59:19,421 --> 00:59:22,191
He didn't hurt Jo Mun Sik
or anything, right?

964
00:59:22,991 --> 00:59:24,721
No. Based on the circumstances,

965
00:59:24,791 --> 00:59:27,031
Jo Mun Sik seems to have died
in an accident.

966
00:59:29,401 --> 00:59:32,871
What about that woman?
What happens to Mi Hyang?

967
00:59:33,831 --> 00:59:35,171
We've opened a public investigation.

968
00:59:35,431 --> 00:59:37,441
A nationwide warrant has been
issued for her.

969
00:59:38,841 --> 00:59:39,871
I see.

970
00:59:44,781 --> 00:59:46,481
If I'm not Jo Mun Sik,

971
00:59:47,651 --> 00:59:49,551
who is the real Jo Mun Sik?

972
00:59:49,621 --> 00:59:53,021
Mi Hyang's late older brother
is Jo Mun Sik.

973
00:59:53,521 --> 00:59:57,091
Do you know where Mi Hyang might be?

974
00:59:57,161 --> 00:59:58,161
Mi Hyang?

975
00:59:58,491 --> 01:00:01,291
Sir, we have to catch Mi Hyang.

976
01:00:01,591 --> 01:00:02,861
Catch Mi Hyang?

977
01:00:02,931 --> 01:00:06,171
We have to. For 30 years,

978
01:00:06,231 --> 01:00:08,271
she kidnapped and imprisoned you.

979
01:00:08,671 --> 01:00:11,801
No. Mi Hyang is my guardian.

980
01:00:11,941 --> 01:00:15,241
Sir, Mi Hyang is a criminal.

981
01:00:15,371 --> 01:00:17,581
She hid your identity...

982
01:00:17,641 --> 01:00:20,351
for 30 years and cut you off
from your family.

983
01:00:20,651 --> 01:00:25,151
Mi Hyang is my sister.
I said she's my sister.

984
01:00:25,221 --> 01:00:28,821
I'm the criminal. I'm the murderer.

985
01:00:29,221 --> 01:00:32,331
- I'm telling you, I'm the murderer!
- Please calm down.

986
01:00:32,391 --> 01:00:33,991
- Father.
- I killed someone.

987
01:00:34,031 --> 01:00:35,391
Father, what's wrong?

988
01:00:35,461 --> 01:00:38,701
We have to hide from the police.
They're coming for me.

989
01:00:39,131 --> 01:00:40,801
- Father.
- We have to run.

990
01:00:40,871 --> 01:00:43,171
- Please calm down.
- Run!

991
01:00:43,241 --> 01:00:45,401
- Father, please!
- Hey!

992
01:00:45,401 --> 01:00:48,011
- Calm down.
- No. They're coming for me.

993
01:00:55,921 --> 01:00:57,151
Let's go.

994
01:01:09,431 --> 01:01:13,071
Father has a classic case
of Stockholm syndrome.

995
01:01:13,871 --> 01:01:17,371
In long-term confinement
or control...

996
01:01:17,601 --> 01:01:19,611
it's a psychological phenomenon...

997
01:01:19,671 --> 01:01:21,471
where victims bond
with their captors.

998
01:01:23,441 --> 01:01:26,051
He was cut off from the world,

999
01:01:26,451 --> 01:01:29,351
so Mi Hyang must have been
his only window to it.

1000
01:01:29,821 --> 01:01:32,851
Even the smallest kindness
felt like salvation...

1001
01:01:33,251 --> 01:01:36,391
and Mi Hyang became
his entire world.

1002
01:02:10,861 --> 01:02:13,531
Health authorities will conduct
an epidemiological investigation...

1003
01:02:13,591 --> 01:02:15,161
to determine exactly what happened.

1004
01:02:15,431 --> 01:02:18,561
In other news, a woman suspected
of holding a man captive...

1005
01:02:18,631 --> 01:02:20,031
for a long time...

1006
01:02:20,101 --> 01:02:22,801
and forcing him to live
as her own brother...

1007
01:02:22,871 --> 01:02:24,371
The woman in her 60s, Jo Mi Hyang...

1008
01:02:24,471 --> 01:02:27,011
has a nationwide warrant
out for her arrest.

1009
01:02:27,071 --> 01:02:29,411
According to the police,
Ms. Jo Mi Hyang...

1010
01:02:29,481 --> 01:02:33,551
kidnapped and confined
a man with amnesia...

1011
01:02:33,611 --> 01:02:36,321
not only forcing him to live
apart from his family...

1012
01:02:36,421 --> 01:02:38,321
but also deceiving him...

1013
01:02:38,381 --> 01:02:40,621
into believing he was her brother
and exploiting his labor.

1014
01:02:40,821 --> 01:02:42,761
- The man managed to escape.
- Mi Hyang?

1015
01:02:42,821 --> 01:02:45,861
He is now under family care.
The police...

1016
01:03:19,461 --> 01:03:20,661
Gi Cheol.

1017
01:03:21,231 --> 01:03:25,531
Gi Cheol?

1018
01:03:26,371 --> 01:03:27,371
Gi Cheol...

1019
01:03:27,371 --> 01:03:29,441
Hey, Jeong Han. Seong Mi.

1020
01:03:29,771 --> 01:03:32,871
- Seong Mi. Jeong Han.
- What is it?

1021
01:03:34,841 --> 01:03:37,441
- Jeong Han. Seong Mi.
- Mother.

1022
01:03:37,511 --> 01:03:38,641
- Mom. What is it?
- I mean...

1023
01:03:38,711 --> 01:03:42,181
He's gone. Your father is gone.

1024
01:03:42,311 --> 01:03:45,481
- What?
- Father's gone?

1025
01:03:45,821 --> 01:03:46,821
What do we do?

1026
01:03:47,621 --> 01:03:49,891
But Father was sleeping.

1027
01:03:50,491 --> 01:03:51,991
- Honey...
- What do we do?

1028
01:03:52,591 --> 01:03:54,491
Where could she be?

1029
01:04:03,301 --> 01:04:04,771
That's Mi Hyang's car.

1030
01:04:07,211 --> 01:04:09,981
Mi Hyang, stop.
You can't get caught.

1031
01:04:09,981 --> 01:04:12,111
Run. It's the police!

1032
01:04:12,181 --> 01:04:14,381
Run!

1033
01:04:46,081 --> 01:04:48,681
(Recipe For Love)

1034
01:04:49,151 --> 01:04:50,351
Director Yang went on
a business trip...

1035
01:04:50,351 --> 01:04:51,981
to Gangwon with CEO Gong.

1036
01:04:52,021 --> 01:04:54,921
- Just the two of them?
- There's only one room?

1037
01:04:56,421 --> 01:04:57,921
Well, then we have no choice.

1038
01:05:00,231 --> 01:05:01,931
I'm crazy.

1039
01:05:02,461 --> 01:05:04,661
I'm crazy about Dong Suk.

1040
01:05:05,461 --> 01:05:08,031
He went back to the person
who locked him up and hit him.

1041
01:05:08,301 --> 01:05:09,871
I just don't get it.

1042
01:05:09,871 --> 01:05:12,641
Jo Mi Hyang is in Onjeong?

1043
01:05:13,071 --> 01:05:16,341
They're tracking her
using nearby CCTV footage.

1044
01:05:16,411 --> 01:05:21,251
I'll ask Jo Mi Hyang myself
why she did that to us.

1045
01:05:21,708 --> 01:05:23,208
Dramaday.me
